---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Compliance Audit Preparation: Getting Ready | Sheepdog" description="Prepare for compliance audits. Learn audit procedures and how to demonstrate control effectiveness to auditors." showMatrix={true}>
  <section>
    <h1>Compliance Audit Preparation: Getting Ready</h1>
    <p class="lead">Compliance audits are coming whether you're ready or not. Preparation is key to passing audits, avoiding findings, and demonstrating control effectiveness. Here's how to get ready.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Types of Compliance Audits</h2>
    
    <h3>External Audits</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>SOC 2:</strong> Trust service criteria for service organizations</li>
      <li><strong>ISO 27001:</strong> Information security management certification</li>
      <li><strong>PCI DSS:</strong> Payment card industry security standards</li>
      <li><strong>HIPAA:</strong> Healthcare data security and privacy</li>
      <li><strong>Regulatory audits:</strong> Government agencies (banking, energy, telecom)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Internal Audits</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Self-assessment of compliance</li>
      <li>Internal audit department review</li>
      <li>Board audit committee oversight</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Audit Preparation Timeline</h2>
    
    <h3>6 Months Before</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Identify which standards apply to your organization</li>
      <li>Assess current controls and gaps</li>
      <li>Develop remediation plan</li>
      <li>Allocate resources and budget</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3 Months Before</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Begin implementing missing controls</li>
      <li>Document all policies and procedures</li>
      <li>Train staff on audit scope</li>
      <li>Conduct internal assessment</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>1 Month Before</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Complete implementation of all controls</li>
      <li>Verify controls are operating effectively</li>
      <li>Gather evidence and documentation</li>
      <li>Brief leadership on audit scope and findings</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Audit Week</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Auditors on-site or remote</li>
      <li>Designate audit coordination team</li>
      <li>Provide access to systems and documentation</li>
      <li>Respond to auditor questions</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Post-Audit</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Review audit findings</li>
      <li>Develop remediation for any findings</li>
      <li>Implement fixes before final report</li>
      <li>Receive certification/approval</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Preparing Audit Evidence</h2>
    
    <h3>Documentation</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Policies and procedures for each control</li>
      <li>Access control lists and approvals</li>
      <li>Training records and sign-offs</li>
      <li>Patch management records</li>
      <li>Incident response documentation</li>
      <li>Security assessments and test results</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>System Logs and Records</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Authentication logs (login activity)</li>
      <li>Authorization logs (access changes)</li>
      <li>Administrative activity logs</li>
      <li>Security events and alerts</li>
      <li>Backup and recovery logs</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Evidence Organization</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Create audit evidence binder or file</li>
      <li>Map evidence to specific controls</li>
      <li>Index for easy reference</li>
      <li>Prepare summary documents</li>
      <li>Brief key personnel on their controls</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Common Audit Findings</h2>
    
    <h3>Control Not Operating Effectively</h3>
    <p>Control exists but isn't working properly:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Example: Access control policy exists but isn't enforced</li>
      <li>Fix: Implement compensating controls, fix the control</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Lack of Documentation</h3>
    <p>Control not documented:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Example: Security training is given but not formally tracked</li>
      <li>Fix: Document and maintain evidence</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Outdated Controls</h3>
    <p>Control doesn't address current threats:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Example: Password policy no longer aligns with best practices</li>
      <li>Fix: Update policy and implement new control</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Scope Gaps</h3>
    <p>Control doesn't apply to all systems:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Example: Patch management applies to some but not all systems</li>
      <li>Fix: Extend control to all affected systems</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Lack of Management Review</h3>
    <p>Control not reviewed for effectiveness:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Fix: Implement quarterly or annual management review</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Audit Coordination</h2>
    
    <h3>Designate an Audit Lead</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Single point of contact for auditors</li>
      <li>Coordinates schedule and logistics</li>
      <li>Tracks auditor requests and evidence</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Prepare Key Personnel</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Brief them on their role in audit</li>
      <li>Answer questions honestly and directly</li>
      <li>Don't try to hide problems</li>
      <li>Focus on control effectiveness, not perfection</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Communicate with Auditors</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide access to systems and data as needed</li>
      <li>Respond to questions promptly</li>
      <li>Offer clarification on processes</li>
      <li>Follow up after audit closes</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Audit Results</h2>
    
    <h3>Clean Audit</h3>
    <p>No findings, controls are operating effectively.</p>

    <h3>Audit with Minor Findings</h3>
    <p>Small gaps or documentation issues that can be fixed quickly.</p>

    <h3>Audit with Major Findings</h3>
    <p>Significant control gaps or non-compliance requiring remediation plan.</p>

    <h3>Failed Audit</h3>
    <p>Critical failures that prevent certification/approval.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Post-Audit</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Review findings and understand requirements</li>
      <li>Develop remediation plan with timelines</li>
      <li>Assign ownership for each remediation</li>
      <li>Implement fixes before deadline</li>
      <li>Provide evidence to auditors before follow-up</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <h2>Prepare for Your Audit</h2>
    <p>Sheepdog Cyber Defense helps organizations assess compliance maturity and prepare for audits. We conduct pre-audit assessments and remediation guidance.</p>
    <a href="/contact" class="btn">Prepare for Your Audit</a>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

